Sentencas: The target of this work is to develop advanced electrode materials with excellent performance compared to conventional cathodes.
Titulo: An Effective Strategy to Enhance the Electrocatalytic Activity of Ruddlesden-Popper Oxides Sr3Fe2O7-δ Electrodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Cobalt-free Ruddlesden-Popper oxides Sr3Fe2-xCuxO7-delta (SFCx, x = 0, 0.1, 0.2) were successfully synthesized and assessed as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: An Effective Strategy to Enhance the Electrocatalytic Activity of Ruddlesden-Popper Oxides Sr3Fe2O7-δ Electrodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Herein, a Cu-doping strategy is shown to increase the electrical conductivity and improve the electrochemical performance of the pristine Sr3Fe2O7-delta.
Titulo: An Effective Strategy to Enhance the Electrocatalytic Activity of Ruddlesden-Popper Oxides Sr3Fe2O7-δ Electrodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Among all the cathode materials, the Sr3Fe1.9Cu0.1O7-delta (SFC10) cathode exhibits the best electrocatalytic activity for oxygen reduction reaction (ORR).
Titulo: An Effective Strategy to Enhance the Electrocatalytic Activity of Ruddlesden-Popper Oxides Sr3Fe2O7-δ Electrodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance is 0.11 omega cm(2) and the peak power density of the single-cell with an SFC10 cathode reaches 955 mW cm(-2) at 700 & DEG;C, a measurement comparable to cobalt-based electrodes.
Titulo: An Effective Strategy to Enhance the Electrocatalytic Activity of Ruddlesden-Popper Oxides Sr3Fe2O7-δ Electrodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The excellent performance is owed to favorable oxygen surface exchange capabilities and larger oxygen vacancy concentrations at elevated temperatures.
Titulo: An Effective Strategy to Enhance the Electrocatalytic Activity of Ruddlesden-Popper Oxides Sr3Fe2O7-δ Electrodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Moreover, the electrochemical impedance spectra and distribution of relaxation time results indicate that the charge transfer process at the triple-phase boundary is the rate-limiting step for ORR on the electrode.
Titulo: An Effective Strategy to Enhance the Electrocatalytic Activity of Ruddlesden-Popper Oxides Sr3Fe2O7-δ Electrodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This work provides an effective strategy for designing novel cathode electrocatalysts for SOFCs.
Titulo: An Effective Strategy to Enhance the Electrocatalytic Activity of Ruddlesden-Popper Oxides Sr3Fe2O7-δ Electrodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
